    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith `nvim-tui`, after `UIEnter` event, `vim.api.nvim_get_chan_info(chan)` data, which can contain the name, is intermittent.\n\nGuess it's a timing problem, `nvim_set_client_info` since docs say\n```\nThe client ... call this after connecting ... Can be called more than once\n```\n\nThere's a further complication in general; this information is not always supported. For reference, `neovide` has `client`, but `client.attributes` is nil. `goneovim` does not have `client`, so the `name` is not available. #31052 discusses getting info about what a client supports, might be a catch-22.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nWith this somewhere in initialization\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"UIEnter\", {\n    callback = function(ev)\n        local chan = vim.v.event.chan\n        local function p(chan) vim.print(string.format(\"'chan info': %s\",\n            vim.inspect(vim.api.nvim_get_chan_info(chan), {newline=\"\"}))) end\n        p(chan)\n        vim.defer_fn(function() p(chan) end, 1000)\n        return true\n    end\n})\n```\nThen run `nvim`.\n\nHere's an example, the first chan info is from the event handler, the second is from a second later.\n```\n'chan info': {  client = vim.empty_dict(),  id = 1,  mode = \"rpc\",  stream = \"stdio\"}\n'chan info': {  client = {    attributes = {      license = \"Apache 2\",      pid = 1247640,      web\nsite = \"https://neovim.io\"    },    methods = vim.empty_dict(),    name = \"nvim-tui\",    type = \"ui\"\n,    version = {      api_compatible = 0,      api_level = 13,      api_prerelease = true,      majo\nr = 0,      minor = 11,      patch = 0,      prerelease = true    }  },  id = 1,  mode = \"rpc\",  str\neam = \"stdio\"}                                                                                      \n```\nSometimes the first line has all the info.\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSome way to find out that there's new information about the client. At least something better than having to poll.\nMaybe an aucmd-event that signals \"new client info available\", with a `v:event` key that says where to look for it; in case `nvim_get_chan_info()` is not the only source?\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/3688a333544251c887d78e6501eec55f0fb685f8\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNA\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nubuntu\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ngnome-terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nmake install",
